<Layout title="Our Story">
    <main data-scroll-container class="pb-12">
        <h1 class="pl-10 pt-24 text-4xl font-bold">About Us</h1>
        <p class="text-xl pl-10 pr-10 whitespace-pre-line">

            Seimei began as a heartfelt journey of rediscovery by Yuki and Hana, two childhood friends from Kyoto. Growing up amidst the serene temples and bustling markets, they were captivated by Japan’s culinary heritage, from the delicate artistry of sushi to the comforting simplicity of miso soup. However, they also saw an opportunity to reimagine these beloved traditions for a modern, sustainable world.

            After years of traveling and experiencing global vegan cuisines, Yuki and Hana returned to Japan with a vision: to create a restaurant that honors traditional Japanese flavors while embracing the plant-based philosophy of mindfulness and harmony. They wanted to share the beauty of their culture with a fresh perspective—one that connects people to the richness of Japanese cuisine without the use of animal products.
            
            Our Philosophy
            At Savor Japan, we believe in the principles of washoku—balance, respect for nature, and a deep appreciation of seasonal ingredients. Every dish on our menu is crafted to reflect the harmony of flavors that Japanese cuisine is known for, while staying true to the compassionate and sustainable values of vegan living.
            
            From the umami-packed ramen broths to the delicate sweetness of matcha desserts, our recipes are inspired by ancient traditions yet tailored for a new generation. By offering plant-based versions of classic dishes, we hope to show that the essence of Japanese cuisine can be celebrated and enjoyed by everyone, regardless of dietary choices.
            
            Why We Do It
            Savor Japan isn’t just a restaurant; it’s a tribute to the beauty of simplicity and the power of innovation. It’s a place where tradition meets creativity, where every dish tells a story of Japan’s rich history and its hopeful future. Whether you’re a lifelong vegan, a curious foodie, or simply someone who appreciates good food, we welcome you to join us on this flavorful journey.
            
            "Savor the art of Japanese cuisine—pure, authentic, and plant-based."            
        </p>

